Singularity Control Center
==========================

About
-----

Singularity Control Center is the primary interface for configuring various
aspects of the Singularity Desktop Environment.

It is conceptually derived from the GNOME 2.32 Control Center, preserving the
modular, capplet-based configuration model, while being adapted for a modern,
composited desktop environment.

Singularity Control Center is NOT a continuation of GNOME 2, but a re-
implementation of its architectural ideas on a GTK3+ stack with client-side
decoration support.


Architecture
------------

- UI model inspired by GNOME 2.32
- Modular configuration capplets
- No shell-specific coupling
- Designed to work in a mutter-compatible, composited environment
- Client-side window decorations (CSD) supported where applicable

This project does not attempt to retrofit mutter or CSD into GNOME 2.
Instead, it reimplements the control-center layer on a modern stack.


Installation
------------

See the file `INSTALL` for build and installation instructions.


Bug Reporting
-------------

Please report bugs using GitHub Issues:

  https://github.com/winhuirass-hue/singularity-control-center/issues

When reporting bugs, include:

- Operating system and version
- Desktop environment and compositor
- Steps to reproduce the issue
- Crash messages or logs, if any
- A stack trace if the issue involves a crash


Getting a Stack Trace
---------------------

If the crash is reproducible, a stack trace is extremely helpful.

Example using gdb:

  gdb singularity-control-center
  (gdb) run
  ... reproduce the crash ...
  (gdb) bt full

Paste the stack trace into the issue or attach it as a file.


Contributing
------------

Patches should be submitted via GitHub Pull Requests.

- Base your work on the `main` branch
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Follow existing code style
- Avoid introducing shell-specific assumptions

For larger changes, please open an issue first to discuss design and scope.


